text.section:
A person may not drive a commercial motor vehicle on any highway or any property specified in § 21-101.1 of this article:
Unless authorized to do so under this title;
While the person's driver's license or privilege to drive is refused in this State or any other state;
While the person's driver's license or privilege to drive is canceled in this State;
While the person's driver's license or privilege to drive is canceled by any other state;
While the person's driver's license or privilege to drive is suspended in this State;
While the person's driver's license or privilege to drive is suspended by any other state;
While the person's driver's license or privilege to drive is revoked in this State;
While the person's driver's license or privilege to drive is revoked by any other state; or
While the person is:
Disqualified from driving a commercial motor vehicle in this State or any other state; or
Disqualified from driving a commercial motor vehicle by the United States Department of Transportation.
